1.title: Screen
1.content: Congrats, you have completed the Stop Signal Task!

content.text:
Part 1: Look at the word on the slide. Press "a" if the word 
you see is an animal, press "n" if the word you 
see is NOT an animal on the next slide that asks "animal or 
non-animal."

For example, if you see the word "seal," press "a" on 
your keyboard.

Press spacebar when you are ready to start.

Part 2: Same as part 1, but now if you see three asterisks,
"***" on the slide, provide no response. The test
will move on to the next slide after an alotted amount of time.

Note: Attempt to go as fast as the previous block. Do not
slow down.

Press spacebar when you are ready to start.

149.title: Intro
149.content:
Stop Signal Task

This task consists of 2 parts: 1) A word will come up on a slide. On the next slide, it will ask you "animal or non-animal." Press the "a" key if that word represents an animal, press the "n" key if the word does NOT represent an animal. 2) Same as the task above, but if there are three asterisks "***" on the slide with the word, provide NO response on the slide next slide that asks you "animal or non-animal." The test will move on to the next word slide after an alotted amount of time. When you're ready, click Continue to start
